      "span_text": "In 2016, a pioneer clinical trial study  has enrolled five patients (4 male and 1 female) affected by complete SCI at the cervical or thoracic level (C5-T12), according to the criteria of the American Spinal Injury Association (ASIA) Impairment Scale, suffering from 2 to 32 months, with an age average comprised from 27 to 56 years."
